     here). Standard Velthuis table (a aa i ii u uu .r .rr .l e ai o au /
     k kh g gh "n / c ch j jh ~n / .t .th .d .dh .n / t th d dh n /
     p ph b bh m / y r l v / "s .s s h / .m .h .a), mapped to SLP1.
     Single INIT state; the transcoder engine picks the longest matching
     entry regardless of file order, so no explicit ordering is required. -->
